@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Dodecagon" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench
must have at least 8 colours.

                             How to play?

  Playing Dodecagon is very simple, click on any of the hexagonal
shaped tiles, except the one shown in colour, which is the
'starting' tile. If a link has not already been formed between
the coloured tile and the one you clicked on, a coloured line,
using the colour of the starting tile, will be formed to link
both tiles, and the tile you clicked on will become the next
starting tile... Note that the colour of a link has no importance
whatsoever, it is just there to add a bit of colour, so to
speak...

  You can move anytime between already linked tiles, but doing so
will waste a move... as the idea of the game is to link all tiles
in the least amount of moves.

  In the center of the game area, a "Best Moves" text displays
the least amount of moves made since the game was run. This
display is then erased when you link the first pair of tiles.

  You can restart a game anytime by clicking on the 'New Game'
button.

  To quit the game, click on the game window's closebutton or press
the 'Esc' key.

  Have fun!

